task.summary:
Rev. 4.2.0
ebc basedirs are read from .ebcconfig in the user's home directory, not longer from environment variable.
Reason: in Mac OSX Yosemite it's quite difficult to set environment variables.
.ebcconfig is an edn file containing a map with key :basedirs and value a vector of directory names as strings.
Catch exception if .ebcconfig does not exist
update Clojure 1.7 Test with transducers in ebc.util
rev 4.4.0 uses pantomime as a wrapper for Apache Tika for text extraction
default content as part of the content
Copyright 2016, minor improvements after linting with eastwood
